cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a declarative approach for specifying service choreographies using a modelling language. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the extension of a modelling language (SBVR) with a notion of time. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper mentions the representation of the SBVR model in formal logic for machine parsing and execution. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper deals with the coordination of participant services in realising a business application scenario. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with the global orderings of invocations on interfaces of participant services.
